    "ingredients_source_text": "- 2 ripe bananas (250 g/9 oz peeled) - 100g (3.5 oz) of oatmeal - 1 table spoon of cinnamon powder (optional) - 1 table spoon of honey (optional)",
    "directions_source_text": "1. Pre-heat the oven to 180\u00b0C (350\u00b0F) 2. Peel the bananas and squash them not too finely in a bowl. 3. Incorporate the oatmeal. 4. Incorporate cinnamon powder and/or honey (optional). 5. On the oven tray, place parchment paper and form discs of the mix, each around 8 cm (3 in) 6. Cook with rotating heat for around 20 minutes, until outside becomes golden and slightly crispy. 7. Eat warm or cold. Can be kept a couple of days in a sealed container."
